# Get a DeepSeek key at https://platform.deepseek.com (the API is OpenAI-compatible).
# Get an Anthropic key at https://console.anthropic.com (used as fallback).

# Copy to .env and fill in. The setup script and Settings loader both reject the
# literal `sk-...` placeholder, so leave it as-is only if you want the friendly
# "edit your .env" prompt the first time you run alfred.
ALFRED_DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=sk-...
# Optional fallback. Leave blank to disable fallback in Slice 1.
ALFRED_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Postgres (defaults match docker-compose.yaml). These mirror the local-dev
# defaults baked into docker-compose.yaml; CHANGE them for any non-dev
# deployment so a leaked compose file isn't also a Postgres credential leak.
POSTGRES_USER=alfred
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=alfred
POSTGRES_DB=alfred

# ALFRED_DATABASE_URL is deliberately LEFT UNSET (commented out).
#
# README says `cp .env.example .env`, and docker-compose forwards this variable
# straight into alfred-core. An uncommented `@localhost:5432` therefore made the
# CONTAINER dial its own loopback, where no Postgres listens — the daemon then
# refused to boot while its message said "verify Postgres is reachable", and it
# was: on `alfred-postgres`, exactly where compose's own default points.
#
# Leave this commented and compose supplies the correct in-network DSN itself:
#   postgresql+asyncpg://${POSTGRES_USER}:${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}@alfred-postgres:5432/${POSTGRES_DB}
#
# Uncomment ONLY for host-side tooling (running alembic or pytest on your machine
# against the published 5432 port rather than inside the stack). If you do, be
# aware the same value is what alfred-core receives — so prefer exporting it in
# your shell for that one command instead of persisting it here.
#ALFRED_DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://alfred:alfred@localhost:5432/alfred

# Operator identity.
ALFRED_OPERATOR_NAME=operator
ALFRED_OPERATOR_LANGUAGE=en-US  # BCP-47; default catalog is English. See Task 3.5.

# Budgets.
ALFRED_DAILY_BUDGET_USD=1.0
ALFRED_PER_CALL_MAX_USD=0.10

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Discord adapter (gateway-hosted, #309 flag-day)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The Discord bot token is read by alfred-core at boot and delivered to the
# gateway-hosted Discord child over fd-3 at spawn time. The gateway and child
# never hold the token in their environment (hard rule #6 / ADR-0036 §5).
# Generate a token at https://discord.com/developers/applications (Bot →
# Reset Token).
#
# WARNING: leaving this blank (or unset) does NOT cleanly disable Discord —
# docker-compose.yaml enables alfred_discord in the gateway's hosted set by
# default, so a missing token triggers a fail-closed "missing_secret" refusal
# that ABORTS the gateway (loud audited refusal; tracked by #331). To run
# without Discord, set ALFRED_GATEWAY_HOSTED_ADAPTERS=[] in .env so the
# gateway starts with an empty hosted-adapter set.
# ALFRED_DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Spec C / G7-1 — egress control plane (the gateway L7 CONNECT forward-proxy)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The gateway is the sole external egress plane. When ALFRED_EGRESS_PROXY_URL is
# set, the core builds provider SDK clients with an httpx proxy pointed at the
# gateway proxy; the gateway enforces a destination allowlist + resolves DNS +
# audits every CONNECT. NOTE: docker-compose.yaml already fills ALFRED_EGRESS_PROXY_URL
# with the gateway default (`${ALFRED_EGRESS_PROXY_URL:-http://alfred-gateway:8889}`), and
# the `:-` form treats an EMPTY `.env` value as unset too — so under compose the stack
# ALWAYS routes through the proxy. G7-3 (ADR-0042) made the proxy MANDATORY: the
# connectivity-free core has NO direct-egress fallback — an unset/empty value fails closed
# at the EgressClient seam (IOPlaneUnavailableError), never a silent direct hop.
#
# The proxy port is NEVER host-published (compose-internal only).
# ALFRED_EGRESS_PROXY_URL=http://alfred-gateway:8889
# ALFRED_EGRESS_PROXY_PORT=8889
# (ALFRED_EGRESS_PROXY_BIND is an advanced, code-default `0.0.0.0` knob read directly
# from the process env; it is intentionally NOT advertised here / NOT forwarded by
# docker-compose — the listener is never host-published, so a compose-level bind
# override has no operational use until the G7-3 internal:true flip changes the model.)
# The core's dialled provider host AND the gateway's allowlist both derive from this;
# compose threads it to BOTH services, so an override here reaches both — otherwise the
# gateway would deny the core's legitimate destination.
# ALFRED_DEEPSEEK_BASE_URL=https://api.deepseek.com/v1

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Spec C / G7-2c — tool-egress relay (the gateway EgressRelay, #333)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The core routes tool egress (e.g. web.fetch) to the gateway EgressRelay over a
# length-prefixed JSON-frame wire (raw asyncio TCP, NOT HTTP). The in-core
# RelayEgressClient parses host:port from ALFRED_EGRESS_RELAY_URL via
# urllib.parse.urlsplit; the http:// scheme prefix is informational only.
#
# The relay port (8890) is NEVER host-published — compose-internal only. The
# destination allowlist and canary tokens are PUBLIC, non-secret (ADR-0036 —
# the gateway holds no vault key).
#
# docker-compose.yaml already fills ALFRED_EGRESS_RELAY_URL on alfred-core
# (${ALFRED_EGRESS_RELAY_URL:-http://alfred-gateway:8890}) and
# ALFRED_EGRESS_RELAY_PORT / ALFRED_TOOL_EGRESS_ALLOWLIST / ALFRED_CANARY_TOKENS
# on alfred-gateway — so under compose these take effect automatically.
#
# Core (the relay client):
# ALFRED_EGRESS_RELAY_URL=http://alfred-gateway:8890
#
# Gateway (the relay server):
# ALFRED_EGRESS_RELAY_PORT=8890
# (ALFRED_EGRESS_RELAY_BIND is an advanced, code-default `0.0.0.0` knob read directly
# from the process env; intentionally NOT advertised here / NOT forwarded by
# docker-compose — the listener is never host-published, so a compose-level bind
# override has no operational use until the G7-3 internal:true flip. Mirrors the
# proxy plane's ALFRED_EGRESS_PROXY_BIND.)
# Tool-egress destination allowlist (empty = default-deny; comma-separated host:port pairs).
# ALFRED_TOOL_EGRESS_ALLOWLIST=
# Canary tokens for the gateway's OUTBOUND exfil scanner (empty = disabled; comma-separated
# strings). Gateway-only — hard-forbidden on the core container
# (tests/unit/test_compose_invariants.py). See ALFRED_WEB_FETCH_CANARY_TOKENS below for the
# distinct core-side INBOUND-reflection canary.
# ALFRED_CANARY_TOKENS=
# #339 PR4a / ADR-0047: core-side INBOUND-reflection canary token source for web.fetch (a
# seeded canary reflected back in a fetched response body). Comma-separated, blanks skipped;
# default empty arms the ResponsePolicy canary seam with a no-op matcher. Distinct from the
# gateway-only ALFRED_CANARY_TOKENS above. Live docker-compose passthrough to alfred-core is
# deferred to #338.
# ALFRED_WEB_FETCH_CANARY_TOKENS=
# G7-4: Discord adapter L7-proxy egress allowlist (gateway-only; empty = built-in
# discord.com + *.discord.gg set is always enforced; this EXTENDS only — ADDS entries,
# never replaces the built-in set; comma-separated host[:port] tokens — non-443
# destinations are expressible as host:port).
# ALFRED_DISCORD_EGRESS_ALLOWLIST=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Slice 3 — trust-boundary configuration
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The Slice-3 plugin transport, capability gate, and supervisor read these.
# Defaults are documented inline. Note: ALFRED_ENV's empty/unset state
# maps to DevGate (development-default, fail-open stubs); set
# ALFRED_ENV=production (or any non-"development" value) explicitly to
# opt into RealGate. See docs/runbooks/slice-3-plugins.md
# §"Capability-gate selection" for the full table.

# Capability-gate selection (src/alfred/bootstrap/gate_factory.py).
# "development" maps to DevGate (fail-open stubs). Unset, empty, or
# whitespace-only ALSO maps to DevGate. Anything else (including typos
# like "prdouction", "prod", "staging") maps to RealGate (production).
# This is opt-OUT of DevGate: set ANY non-development value to get the
# safer RealGate behaviour. See docs/runbooks/slice-3-plugins.md
# §"Capability-gate selection" for the full table.
# ALFRED_ENV=production

# Runtime environment. One of: development, production, test. Gates production
# safety refusals (sec-002). Precedence: ALFRED_ENVIRONMENT env var >
# /etc/alfred/environment > this .env file. DISTINCT from ALFRED_ENV above
# (the capability-gate selector) — different variable, different purpose.
ALFRED_ENVIRONMENT=production

# Sandbox policy directory consulted by bin/alfred-plugin-launcher.sh. The
# launcher reads <DIR>/<plugin_id>.policy and refuses to spawn if the file
# is missing (production fail-closed). Default: /etc/alfred/sandbox.
# ALFRED_SANDBOX_POLICY_DIR=/etc/alfred/sandbox

# Target UID for the runuser-based UID drop on Linux (sec-003). Provision
# this account before deploying — the runbook has the systemd-sysusers
# fragment. Default: alfred-quarantine.
# ALFRED_PLUGIN_UID=alfred-quarantine

# Dev-only escape hatch: with ALFRED_ENV=development AND this set to "1",
# the launcher spawns plugins without a sandbox policy and emits a
# supervisor.config_insecure audit JSON line. REFUSED unconditionally in
# production — sec-003. Leave unset outside development.
# ALFRED_PLUGIN_LAUNCHER_UNSANDBOXED=0

# Perf-gate force-run flag. The hook-dispatch perf suite refuses to run
# at load >= 1.0 x CPU count (warns at 0.7) so flaky CI runners don't
# burn time on noise. CI sets this to "1" to opt OUT of the guard;
# contributors can set "1"/"true"/"yes" (case-insensitive) to do the same
# locally. See docs/ci/required-checks.md.
# ALFRED_TEST_PERF_FORCE=0

# Redis maxmemory cap (docker-compose). The default 256mb suits a
# single-operator deployment; tune up for larger households. See PR-S3-0b
# spec for the volatile-lru eviction policy this couples with.
# ALFRED_REDIS_MAXMEMORY=256mb

# Grafana admin username — defaults to `admin`; uncomment to override.
# GF_SECURITY_ADMIN_USER=admin
# Grafana admin password — auto-generated by bin/alfred-setup.sh on first run (never commit a real value).
GF_SECURITY_ADMIN_PASSWORD=

# State-git path — where the reviewer-gated proposal flow stores branch
# state. Default: /var/lib/alfred/state.git. The seed script
# (bin/alfred-state-git-seed.sh) initialises this on first deploy.
# STATE_GIT_PATH=/var/lib/alfred/state.git

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Slice 3 — quarantined LLM (PR-S3-4)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The quarantined-LLM plugin (src/alfred/security/quarantine_child/) reads its
# provider, model, and secret from config/routing.yaml [quarantine]. These
# env vars configure the SecretBroker entry that the routing.yaml secret_id
# references. See docs/runbooks/slice-3-quarantined-llm.md for the full
# setup walkthrough, including OS-user provisioning and fd-3 key delivery.
#
# Provider selection: routing.yaml [quarantine] is the source of truth. The
# three supported values for .provider are "anthropic", "deepseek", "openai".
# The quarantined provider SHOULD differ from the privileged provider
# (defence-in-depth, spec §5.4) — e.g. if ALFRED_DEEPSEEK_API_KEY above
# is the privileged key, use Anthropic here, and vice versa.
#
# There are NO ALFRED_QUARANTINED_PROVIDER / ALFRED_QUARANTINED_MODEL env vars.
# Earlier revisions of this file documented them; nothing has ever read them, so
# setting them did nothing. Edit config/routing.yaml [quarantine] instead (the
# model there is currently claude-haiku-4-5). Note the model + token budget are
# additionally mirrored by drift-guarded constants in
# src/alfred/comms_mcp/daemon_runtime.py until the routing.yaml loader lands, so
# changing the model means changing BOTH (a test enforces they agree).
#
# REQUIRED since #340 PR2b-golive — a keyless stack REFUSES TO BOOT.
# The quarantined (dual-LLM) child now makes real provider calls, so the core
# resolves this key before spawning it and exits 2 with
# `quarantine_provider_key_unset` when it is missing. That is deliberate: a real
# client on a placeholder key would be a silent dead-LLM. Under `docker compose
# up` the stack will crash-loop until you set it here.
#
# Secret broker registration: the routing.yaml secret_id value
# ("quarantine_provider_api_key") must appear in SUPPORTED_SECRETS. The
# env-backend reads ALFRED_<UPPERCASED_SECRET_ID>, which for the default
# secret_id is the variable below. Set it in THIS file (docker-compose forwards
# it to alfred-core); alfred-core mounts no secrets.toml, so there is no file
# route for this particular key.
ALFRED_QUARANTINE_PROVIDER_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CI — nightly real-LLM smoke (#339 PR4c)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Throwaway low-balance DeepSeek (deepseek-chat) key for the nightly real-LLM
# act-loop smoke (tests/integration/orchestrator/test_act_loop_real_llm_smoke.py).
# Nightly-only + skip-unless-set — never spends on a per-commit lane or fork PR.
ALFRED_SMOKE_PROVIDER_KEY=
